igee.org - planing,recording and sharing your good action.

powered by Ruby on Rails 3

Step 1: clone repository
  git clone git://github.com/igee/igee.git

Setp 2: install dependent gems
  cd igee
  bundle install

Step 3: edit your database configuration file
  cp config/database.yml.sample config/database.yml
  vi config/database.yml

Step 4: edit your local config file
  cp config/config.yml.sample config/config.yml
  vi config/config.yml
 
Step 5: db migration & load fixtures and seed
  rake db:create
  rake db:auto:migrate
  rake db:fixtures:load FIXTURES_PATH=db/fixtures
  rake db:seed
  
Step 6: Go!launch igee!
  rails s  
